# PFNA and PFDA data
pfna_da <- fread("pfas_methyl_di4.csv")
## pid, pfoa concentration and cpg M values, and clinical
## gender information
pid583 <- fread("/home/guanshim/Documents/gitlab/ECCHO_github/DataRaw/pid583.csv")
pid583 <- as.vector(unlist(pid583))
# check pid
sum(pfna_da$pid != pid583)
## [1] 0
# ln transform
pfna_da_ln <- pfna_da %>% dplyr::mutate(lnpfdea = log(PFDEA_ng_ml, 
    base = exp(1)), lnpfna = log(PFNA2_ng_ml, base = exp(1)))

new_chem <- c("PFDEA_ng_ml", "PFNA2_ng_ml")
##### Female data ##### infant_sex == 2 male infant_sex == 1
##### female get female data
pfna_da_f <- pfna_da_ln %>% dplyr::filter(pid %in% pid583) %>% 
    dplyr::filter(infant_sex == 1)
dim(pfna_da_f)
## [1] 278  30
clin_chem_f <- read.csv("/home/guanshim/Documents/gitlab/ECCHO_github/DataProcessed/clin_chem_f.csv")
sum(clin_chem_f$pid != pfna_da_f$pid)
## [1] 0
# get male data
pfna_da_m <- pfna_da_ln %>% dplyr::filter(pid %in% pid583) %>%

## [1] 305  30

# attach new data to old data
clin_chem_f_nada <- clin_chem_f %>% dplyr::mutate(lnpfdea = pfna_da_f$lnpfdea,

    lnpfna = pfna_da_m$lnpfna)
